property.shortdesc: The hash of this search results. Identical hashes lead to the exact same rendition of an item in the UI.

property.shortdesc: The payload of the search result in JSON string format. The payload contains all data that is needed to get the actual referenced object of this search result.

property.name: score
property.shortdesc: The score for the search result in range [01]. Higher numbers indicate a better match. Search agents that only match on exact hits will only return 1.0 as score for best matches.

property.name: type
property.shortdesc: The type of this search result. This can be e.g. 'MasterClip' 'Marker'...

property.name: universalJoinHash
property.shortdesc: The hash of the object this search results is referring to. Generally if two search results are referencing the same object regardless of modality or details they will feature an identical universalJoinHash. A good example would be the same project item referenced by metadata and transcript search would lead to the same universalJoinHash.
